    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Polymerized methyl methacrylate is a compound having a hard and glasslike appearance, with softening temperature from 105-125 C. Classified as bioinert. As a resin, widely used as a glass substitute (e.g., Plexiglass (TM)) and a bonelike material for prosthetics. First commercially sold in 1933 as a glass substitute.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
